headline: Kenin Surges Past Barty and Reaches Final
abstract: Kenin, an American seeded 14th, will face unseeded Garbiñe Muguruza in the final on Saturday.
lead_paragraph: MELBOURNE, Australia — This country’s biggest hopes in decades for a homegrown Australian Open singles champion ended in the semifinals on Thursday when top-seeded Ashleigh Barty lost to an American, Sofia Kenin, 7-6 (6), 7-5.
